he book of the generation of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Abraham begat Isaac; and Isaac begat Jacob; and Jacob begat Judas and his brethren;
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And Judas begat Phares and Zara of Thamar; and Phares begat Esrom; and Esrom begat Aram;
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And Aram begat Aminadab; and Aminadab begat Naasson; and Naasson begat Salmon;
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]And Salmon begat Booz of Rachab; and Booz begat Obed of Ruth; and Obed begat Jesse;
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]And Jesse begat David the king; and David the king begat Solomon of her that had been the wife of Urias;
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]And Solomon begat Roboam; and Roboam begat Abia; and Abia begat Asa;
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]And Asa begat Josaphat; and Josaphat begat Joram; and Joram begat Ozias;
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]And Ozias begat Joatham; and Joatham begat Achaz; and Achaz begat Ezekias;
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]And Ezekias begat Manasses; and Manasses begat Amon; and Amon begat Josias;
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And Josias begat Jechonias and his brethren, about the time they were carried away to Babylon:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And after they were brought to Babylon, Jechonias begat Salathiel; and Salathiel begat Zorobabel;
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And Zorobabel begat Abiud; and Abiud begat Eliakim; and Eliakim begat Azor;
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]And Azor begat Sadoc; and Sadoc begat Achim; and Achim begat Eliud;
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And Eliud begat Eleazar; and Eleazar begat Matthan; and Matthan begat Jacob;
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And Jacob begat Joseph the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]So all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen generations; and from David until the carrying away into Babylon are fourteen generations; and from the carrying away into Babylon unto Christ are fourteen generations.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Now the birth of Jesus Christ was on this wise: When as his mother Mary was espoused to Joseph, before they came together, she was found with child of the Holy Ghost.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Then Joseph her husband, being a just man, and not willing to make her a public example, was minded to put her away privily.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]But while he thought on these things, behold, the angel of the Lord appeared unto him in a dream, saying, Joseph, thou son of David, fear not to take unto thee Mary thy wife: for that which is conceived in her is of the Holy Ghost.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And she shall bring forth a son, and thou shalt call his name Jesus : for he shall save his people from their sins.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Now all this was done, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet, saying,
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel, which being interpreted is, God with us.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Then Joseph being raised from sleep did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him, and took unto him his wife:
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And knew her not till she had brought forth her firstborn son: and he called his name Jesus .
