.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "J" 2 COND 90
udge not, that ye be not judged.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]For with what judgment ye judge, ye shall be judged: and with what measure ye mete, it shall be measured to you again.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother's eye, but considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye?
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]Or how wilt thou say to thy brother, Let me pull out the mote out of thine eye; and, behold, a beam is in thine own eye?
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Thou hypocrite, first cast out the beam out of thine own eye; and then shalt thou see clearly to cast out the mote out of thy brother's eye.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Give not that which is holy unto the dogs, neither cast ye your pearls before swine, lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Ask, and it shall be given you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you:
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]For every one that asketh receiveth; and he that seeketh findeth; and to him that knocketh it shall be opened.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Or what man is there of you, whom if his son ask bread, will he give him a stone?
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Or if he ask a fish, will he give him a serpent?
