\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]But he said, Nay; lest while ye gather up the tares, ye root up also the wheat with them.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Let both grow together until the harvest: and in the time of harvest I will say to the reapers, Gather ye together first the tares, and bind them in bundles to burn them: but gather the wheat into my barn.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Another parable put he forth unto them, saying, The kingdom of heaven is like to a grain of mustard seed, which a man took, and sowed in his field:
