nd Jesus went out, and departed from the temple: and his disciples came to him for to shew him the buildings of the temple.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And Jesus said unto them, See ye not all these things? verily I say unto you, There shall not be left here one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And as he sat upon the mount of Olives, the disciples came unto him privately, saying, Tell us, when shall these things be? and what shall be the sign of thy coming, and of the end of the world?
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And Jesus answered and said unto them, Take heed that no man deceive you.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]For many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and shall deceive many.
