\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]His lord said unto him, Well done, thou good and faithful servant: thou hast been faithful over a few things, I will make thee ruler over many things: enter thou into the joy of thy lord.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]He also that had received two talents came and said, Lord, thou deliveredst unto me two talents: behold, I have gained two other talents beside them.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]His lord said unto him, Well done, good and faithful servant; thou hast been faithful over a few things, I will make thee ruler over many things: enter thou into the joy of thy lord.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Then he which had received the one talent came and said, Lord, I knew thee that thou art an hard man, reaping where thou hast not sown, and gathering where thou hast not strawed:
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And I was afraid, and went and hid thy talent in the earth: lo, there thou hast that is thine.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]His lord answered and said unto him, Thou wicked and slothful servant, thou knewest that I reap where I sowed not, and gather where I have not strawed:
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]Thou oughtest therefore to have put my money to the exchangers, and then at my coming I should have received mine own with usury.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Take therefore the talent from him, and give it unto him which hath ten talents.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]For unto every one that hath shall be given, and he shall have abundance: but from him that hath not shall be taken away even that which he hath.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]And cast ye the unprofitable servant into outer darkness: there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]When the Son of man shall come in his glory, and all the holy angels with him, then shall he sit upon the throne of his glory:
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]And before him shall be gathered all nations: and he shall separate them one from another, as a shepherd divideth his sheep from the goats:
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]And he shall set the sheep on his right hand, but the goats on the left.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Then shall the King say unto them on his right hand, Come, ye blessed of my Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world:
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]For I was an hungred, and ye gave me meat: I was thirsty, and ye gave me drink: I was a stranger, and ye took me in:
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]Naked, and ye clothed me: I was sick, and ye visited me: I was in prison, and ye came unto me.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]Then shall the righteous answer him, saying, Lord, when saw we thee an hungred, and fed thee? or thirsty, and gave thee drink?
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]When saw we thee a stranger, and took thee in? or naked, and clothed thee?
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]Or when saw we thee sick, or in prison, and came unto thee?
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]And the King shall answer and say unto them, Verily I say unto you, Inasmuch as ye have done it unto one of the least of these my brethren, ye have done it unto me.
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]Then shall he say also unto them on the left hand, Depart from me, ye cursed, into everlasting fire, prepared for the devil and his angels:
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]For I was an hungred, and ye gave me no meat: I was thirsty, and ye gave me no drink:
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]I was a stranger, and ye took me not in: naked, and ye clothed me not: sick, and in prison, and ye visited me not.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]Then shall they also answer him, saying, Lord, when saw we thee an hungred, or athirst, or a stranger, or naked, or sick, or in prison, and did not minister unto thee?
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]Then shall he answer them, saying, Verily I say unto you, Inasmuch as ye did it not to one of the least of these, ye did it not to me.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]And these shall go away into everlasting punishment: but the righteous into life eternal.
