\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Peter answered and said unto him, Though all men shall be offended because of thee, yet will I never be offended.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto thee, That this night, before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]Peter said unto him, Though I should die with thee, yet will I not deny thee. Likewise also said all the disciples.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]Then cometh Jesus with them unto a place called Gethsemane, and saith unto the disciples, Sit ye here, while I go and pray yonder.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And he took with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, and began to be sorrowful and very heavy.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]Then saith he unto them, My soul is exceeding sorrowful, even unto death: tarry ye here, and watch with me.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]And he went a little farther, and fell on his face, and prayed, saying, O my Father, if it be possible, let this cup pass from me: nevertheless not as I will, but as thou wilt.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]And he cometh unto the disciples, and findeth them asleep, and saith unto Peter, What, could ye not watch with me one hour?
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]Watch and pray, that ye enter not into temptation: the spirit indeed is willing, but the flesh is weak.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]He went away again the second time, and prayed, saying, O my Father, if this cup may not pass away from me, except I drink it, thy will be done.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]And he came and found them asleep again: for their eyes were heavy.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]And he left them, and went away again, and prayed the third time, saying the same words.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]Then cometh he to his disciples, and saith unto them, Sleep on now, and take your rest: behold, the hour is at hand, and the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]Rise, let us be going: behold, he is at hand that doth betray me.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]And while he yet spake, lo, Judas, one of the twelve, came, and with him a great multitude with swords and staves, from the chief priests and elders of the people.
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]Now he that betrayed him gave them a sign, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he: hold him fast.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]And forthwith he came to Jesus, and said, Hail, master; and kissed him.
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]And Jesus said unto him, Friend, wherefore art thou come? Then came they, and laid hands on Jesus and took him.
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX]And, behold, one of them which were with Jesus stretched out his hand, and drew his sword, and struck a servant of the high priest's, and smote off his ear.
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]Then said Jesus unto him, Put up again thy sword into his place: for all they that take the sword shall perish with the sword.
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]Thinkest thou that I cannot now pray to my Father, and he shall presently give me more than twelve legions of angels?
\*[SUP]54\*[SUPX]But how then shall the scriptures be fulfilled, that thus it must be?
\*[SUP]55\*[SUPX]In that same hour said Jesus to the multitudes, Are ye come out as against a thief with swords and staves for to take me? I sat daily with you teaching in the temple, and ye laid no hold on me.
\*[SUP]56\*[SUPX]But all this was done, that the scriptures of the prophets might be fulfilled. Then all the disciples forsook him, and fled.
\*[SUP]57\*[SUPX]And they that had laid hold on Jesus led him away to Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and the elders were assembled.
\*[SUP]58\*[SUPX]But Peter followed him afar off unto the high priest's palace, and went in, and sat with the servants, to see the end.
\*[SUP]59\*[SUPX]Now the chief priests, and elders, and all the council, sought false witness against Jesus, to put him to death;
\*[SUP]60\*[SUPX]But found none: yea, though many false witnesses came, yet found they none. At the last came two false witnesses,
\*[SUP]61\*[SUPX]And said, This fellow said, I am able to destroy the temple of God, and to build it in three days.
\*[SUP]62\*[SUPX]And the high priest arose, and said unto him, Answerest thou nothing? what is it which these witness against thee?
\*[SUP]63\*[SUPX]But Jesus held his peace, And the high priest answered and said unto him, I adjure thee by the living God, that thou tell us whether thou be the Christ, the Son of God.
\*[SUP]64\*[SUPX]Jesus saith unto him, Thou hast said: nevertheless I say unto you, Hereafter shall ye see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven.
\*[SUP]65\*[SUPX]Then the high priest rent his clothes, saying, He hath spoken blasphemy; what further need have we of witnesses? behold, now ye have heard his blasphemy.
\*[SUP]66\*[SUPX]What think ye? They answered and said, He is guilty of death.
\*[SUP]67\*[SUPX]Then did they spit in his face, and buffeted him; and others smote him with the palms of their hands,
\*[SUP]68\*[SUPX]Saying, Prophesy unto us, thou Christ, Who is he that smote thee?
\*[SUP]69\*[SUPX]Now Peter sat without in the palace: and a damsel came unto him, saying, Thou also wast with Jesus of Galilee.
\*[SUP]70\*[SUPX]But he denied before them all, saying, I know not what thou sayest.
\*[SUP]71\*[SUPX]And when he was gone out into the porch, another maid saw him, and said unto them that were there, This fellow was also with Jesus of Nazareth.
\*[SUP]72\*[SUPX]And again he denied with an oath, I do not know the man.
\*[SUP]73\*[SUPX]And after a while came unto him they that stood by, and said to Peter, Surely thou also art one of them; for thy speech bewrayeth thee.
\*[SUP]74\*[SUPX]Then began he to curse and to swear, saying, I know not the man. And immediately the cock crew.
\*[SUP]75\*[SUPX]And Peter remembered the word of Jesus, which said unto him, Before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice. And he went out, and wept bitterly.
