nd again he entered into Capernaum after some days; and it was noised that he was in the house.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And straightway many were gathered together, insomuch that there was no room to receive them, no, not so much as about the door: and he preached the word unto them.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And they come unto him, bringing one sick of the palsy, which was borne of four.
