\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]And if thine eye offend thee, pluck it out: it is better for thee to enter into the kingdom of God with one eye, than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire:
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]For every one shall be salted with fire, and every sacrifice shall be salted with salt.
