\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power upon earth to forgive sins, (he said unto the sick of the palsy,) I say unto thee, Arise, and take up thy couch, and go into thine house.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And immediately he rose up before them, and took up that whereon he lay, and departed to his own house, glorifying God.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And they were all amazed, and they glorified God, and were filled with fear, saying, We have seen strange things to day.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And after these things he went forth, and saw a publican, named Levi, sitting at the receipt of custom: and he said unto him, Follow me.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And he left all, rose up, and followed him.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And Levi made him a great feast in his own house: and there was a great company of publicans and of others that sat down with them.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]But their scribes and Pharisees murmured against his disciples, saying, Why do ye eat and drink with publicans and sinners?
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]And Jesus answering said unto them, They that are whole need not a physician; but they that are sick.
