\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And he spake also a parable unto them; No man putteth a piece of a new garment upon an old; if otherwise, then both the new maketh a rent, and the piece that was taken out of the new agreeth not with the old.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And no man putteth new wine into old bottles; else the new wine will burst the bottles, and be spilled, and the bottles shall perish.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]But new wine must be put into new bottles; and both are preserved.
