\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And he said unto Jesus, Lord, remember me when thou comest into thy kingdom.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]And Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto thee, Today shalt thou be with me in paradise.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]And it was about the sixth hour, and there was a darkness over all the earth until the ninth hour.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]And the sun was darkened, and the veil of the temple was rent in the midst.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]And when Jesus had cried with a loud voice, he said, Father, into thy hands I commend my spirit: and having said thus, he gave up the ghost.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]Now when the centurion saw what was done, he glorified God, saying, Certainly this was a righteous man.
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]And all the people that came together to that sight, beholding the things which were done, smote their breasts, and returned.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]And all his acquaintance, and the women that followed him from Galilee, stood afar off, beholding these things.
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]And, behold, there was a man named Joseph, a counsellor; and he was a good man, and a just:
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX](The same had not consented to the counsel and deed of them;) he was of Arimathaea, a city of the Jews: who also himself waited for the kingdom of God.
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]This man went unto Pilate, and begged the body of Jesus.
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]And he took it down, and wrapped it in linen, and laid it in a sepulchre that was hewn in stone, wherein never man before was laid.
\*[SUP]54\*[SUPX]And that day was the preparation, and the sabbath drew on.
\*[SUP]55\*[SUPX]And the women also, which came with him from Galilee, followed after, and beheld the sepulchre, and how his body was laid.
\*[SUP]56\*[SUPX]And they returned, and prepared spices and ointments; and rested the sabbath day according to the commandment.
