\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Saying, The Son of man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified, and the third day rise again.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]And they remembered his words,
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]And returned from the sepulchre, and told all these things unto the eleven, and to all the rest.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]It was Mary Magdalene and Joanna, and Mary the mother of James, and other women that were with them, which told these things unto the apostles.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And their words seemed to them as idle tales, and they believed them not.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Then arose Peter, and ran unto the sepulchre; and stooping down, he beheld the linen clothes laid by themselves, and departed, wondering in himself at that which was come to pass.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And, behold, two of them went that same day to a village called Emmaus, which was from Jerusalem about threescore furlongs.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]And they talked together of all these things which had happened.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And it came to pass, that, while they communed together and reasoned, Jesus himself drew near, and went with them.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]But their eyes were holden that they should not know him.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And he said unto them, What manner of communications are these that ye have one to another, as ye walk, and are sad?
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And the one of them, whose name was Cleopas, answering said unto him, Art thou only a stranger in Jerusalem, and hast not known the things which are come to pass there in these days?
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]And he said unto them, What things? And they said unto him, Concerning Jesus of Nazareth, which was a prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people:
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And how the chief priests and our rulers delivered him to be condemned to death, and have crucified him.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]But we trusted that it had been he which should have redeemed Israel: and beside all this, to day is the third day since these things were done.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Yea, and certain women also of our company made us astonished, which were early at the sepulchre;
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And when they found not his body, they came, saying, that they had also seen a vision of angels, which said that he was alive.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And certain of them which were with us went to the sepulchre, and found it even so as the women had said: but him they saw not.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Then he said unto them, O fools, and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken:
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Ought not Christ to have suffered these things, and to enter into his glory?
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And beginning at Moses and all the prophets, he expounded unto them in all the scriptures the things concerning himself.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And they drew nigh unto the village, whither they went: and he made as though he would have gone further.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]But they constrained him, saying, Abide with us: for it is toward evening, and the day is far spent. And he went in to tarry with them.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]And it came to pass, as he sat at meat with them, he took bread, and blessed it, and brake, and gave to them.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]And their eyes were opened, and they knew him; and he vanished out of their sight.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]And they said one to another, Did not our heart burn within us, while he talked with us by the way, and while he opened to us the scriptures?
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]And they rose up the same hour, and returned to Jerusalem, and found the eleven gathered together, and them that were with them,
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Saying, The Lord is risen indeed, and hath appeared to Simon.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]And they told what things were done in the way, and how he was known of them in breaking of bread.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And as they thus spake, Jesus himself stood in the midst of them, and saith unto them, Peace be unto you.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]But they were terrified and affrighted, and supposed that they had seen a spirit.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]And he said unto them, Why are ye troubled? and why do thoughts arise in your hearts?
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]Behold my hands and my feet, that it is I myself: handle me, and see; for a spirit hath not flesh and bones, as ye see me have.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]And when he had thus spoken, he shewed them his hands and his feet.
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]And while they yet believed not for joy, and wondered, he said unto them, Have ye here any meat?
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And they gave him a piece of a broiled fish, and of an honeycomb.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]And he took it, and did eat before them.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]And he said unto them, These are the words which I spake unto you, while I was yet with you, that all things must be fulfilled, which were written in the law of Moses, and in the prophets, and in the psalms, concerning me.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]Then opened he their understanding, that they might understand the scriptures,
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]And said unto them, Thus it is written, and thus it behooved Christ to suffer, and to rise from the dead the third day:
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]And that repentance and remission of sins should be preached in his name among all nations, beginning at Jerusalem.
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]And ye are witnesses of these things.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]And, behold, I send the promise of my Father upon you: but tarry ye in the city of Jerusalem, until ye be endued with power from on high.
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]And he led them out as far as to Bethany, and he lifted up his hands, and blessed them.
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX]And it came to pass, while he blessed them, he was parted from them, and carried up into heaven.
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]And they worshipped him, and returned to Jerusalem with great joy:
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]And were continually in the temple, praising and blessing God. Amen.
