\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]But he spake of the temple of his body.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]When therefore he was risen from the dead, his disciples remembered that he had said this unto them; and they believed the scripture, and the word which Jesus had said.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Now when he was in Jerusalem at the passover, in the feast day, many believed in his name, when they saw the miracles which he did.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]But Jesus did not commit himself unto them, because he knew all men,
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And needed not that any should testify of man: for he knew what was in man.
