\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Our fathers worshipped in this mountain; and ye say, that in Jerusalem is the place where men ought to worship.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Jesus saith unto her, Woman, believe me, the hour cometh, when ye shall neither in this mountain, nor yet at Jerusalem, worship the Father.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Ye worship ye know not what: we know what we worship: for salvation is of the Jews.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]But the hour cometh, and now is, when the true worshippers shall worship the Father in spirit and in truth: for the Father seeketh such to worship him.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]God is a Spirit: and they that worship him must worship him in spirit and in truth.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]The woman saith unto him, I know that Messias cometh, which is called Christ: when he is come, he will tell us all things.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Jesus saith unto her, I that speak unto thee am he.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And upon this came his disciples, and marvelled that he talked with the woman: yet no man said, What seekest thou? or, Why talkest thou with her?
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]The woman then left her waterpot, and went her way into the city, and saith to the men,
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Come, see a man, which told me all things that ever I did: is not this the Christ?
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Then they went out of the city, and came unto him.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]In the mean while his disciples prayed him, saying, Master, eat.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]But he said unto them, I have meat to eat that ye know not of.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Therefore said the disciples one to another, Hath any man brought him ought to eat?
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Jesus saith unto them, My meat is to do the will of him that sent me, and to finish his work.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]Say not ye, There are yet four months, and then cometh harvest? behold, I say unto you, Lift up your eyes, and look on the fields; for they are white already to harvest.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And he that reapeth receiveth wages, and gathereth fruit unto life eternal: that both he that soweth and he that reapeth may rejoice together.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And herein is that saying true, One soweth, and another reapeth.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]I sent you to reap that whereon ye bestowed no labour: other men laboured, and ye are entered into their labours.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]And many of the Samaritans of that city believed on him for the saying of the woman, which testified, He told me all that ever I did.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]So when the Samaritans were come unto him, they besought him that he would tarry with them: and he abode there two days.
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]And many more believed because of his own word;
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And said unto the woman, Now we believe, not because of thy saying: for we have heard him ourselves, and know that this is indeed the Christ, the Saviour of the world.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]Now after two days he departed thence, and went into Galilee.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]For Jesus himself testified, that a prophet hath no honour in his own country.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]Then when he was come into Galilee, the Galilaeans received him, having seen all the things that he did at Jerusalem at the feast: for they also went unto the feast.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]So Jesus came again into Cana of Galilee, where he made the water wine. And there was a certain nobleman, whose son was sick at Capernaum.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]When he heard that Jesus was come out of Judaea into Galilee, he went unto him, and besought him that he would come down, and heal his son: for he was at the point of death.
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]Then said Jesus unto him, Except ye see signs and wonders, ye will not believe.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]The nobleman saith unto him, Sir, come down ere my child die.
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]Jesus saith unto him, Go thy way; thy son liveth. And the man believed the word that Jesus had spoken unto him, and he went his way.
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX]And as he was now going down, his servants met him, and told him, saying, Thy son liveth.
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]Then enquired he of them the hour when he began to amend. And they said unto him, Yesterday at the seventh hour the fever left him.
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]So the father knew that it was at the same hour, in the which Jesus said unto him, Thy son liveth: and himself believed, and his whole house.
\*[SUP]54\*[SUPX]This is again the second miracle that Jesus did, when he was come out of Judaea into Galilee.
