fter this there was a feast of the Jews; and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Now there is at Jerusalem by the sheep market a pool, which is called in the Hebrew tongue Bethesda, having five porches.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]In these lay a great multitude of impotent folk, of blind, halt, withered, waiting for the moving of the water.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]For an angel went down at a certain season into the pool, and troubled the water: whosoever then first after the troubling of the water stepped in was made whole of whatsoever disease he had.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]And a certain man was there, which had an infirmity thirty and eight years.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]When Jesus saw him lie, and knew that he had been now a long time in that case, he saith unto him, Wilt thou be made whole?
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]The impotent man answered him, Sir, I have no man, when the water is troubled, to put me into the pool: but while I am coming, another steppeth down before me.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Jesus saith unto him, Rise, take up thy bed, and walk.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]And immediately the man was made whole, and took up his bed, and walked: and on the same day was the sabbath.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]The Jews therefore said unto him that was cured, It is the sabbath day: it is not lawful for thee to carry thy bed.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]He answered them, He that made me whole, the same said unto me, Take up thy bed, and walk.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Then asked they him, What man is that which said unto thee, Take up thy bed, and walk?
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And he that was healed wist not who it was: for Jesus had conveyed himself away, a multitude being in that place.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Afterward Jesus findeth him in the temple, and said unto him, Behold, thou art made whole: sin no more, lest a worse thing come unto thee.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]The man departed, and told the Jews that it was Jesus, which had made him whole.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And therefore did the Jews persecute Jesus, and sought to slay him, because he had done these things on the sabbath day.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]But Jesus answered them, My Father worketh hitherto, and I work.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Therefore the Jews sought the more to kill him, because he not only had broken the sabbath, but said also that God was his Father, making himself equal with God.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Then answered Jesus and said unto them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, The Son can do nothing of himself, but what he seeth the Father do: for what things soever he doeth, these also doeth the Son likewise.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]For the Father loveth the Son, and sheweth him all things that himself doeth: and he will shew him greater works than these, that ye may marvel.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]For as the Father raiseth up the dead, and quickeneth them; even so the Son quickeneth whom he will.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]For the Father judgeth no man, but hath committed all judgment unto the Son:
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]That all men should honour the Son, even as they honour the Father. He that honoureth not the Son honoureth not the Father which hath sent him.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that heareth my word, and believeth on him that sent me, hath everlasting life, and shall not come into condemnation; but is passed from death unto life.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Verily, verily, I say unto you, The hour is coming, and now is, when the dead shall hear the voice of the Son of God: and they that hear shall live.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]For as the Father hath life in himself; so hath he given to the Son to have life in himself;
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And hath given him authority to execute judgment also, because he is the Son of man.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Marvel not at this: for the hour is coming, in the which all that are in the graves shall hear his voice,
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And shall come forth; they that have done good, unto the resurrection of life; and they that have done evil, unto the resurrection of damnation.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]I can of mine own self do nothing: as I hear, I judge: and my judgment is just; because I seek not mine own will, but the will of the Father which hath sent me.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]If I bear witness of myself, my witness is not true.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]There is another that beareth witness of me; and I know that the witness which he witnesseth of me is true.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Ye sent unto John, and he bare witness unto the truth.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]But I receive not testimony from man: but these things I say, that ye might be saved.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]He was a burning and a shining light: and ye were willing for a season to rejoice in his light.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]But I have greater witness than that of John: for the works which the Father hath given me to finish, the same works that I do, bear witness of me, that the Father hath sent me.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And the Father himself, which hath sent me, hath borne witness of me. Ye have neither heard his voice at any time, nor seen his shape.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]And ye have not his word abiding in you: for whom he hath sent, him ye believe not.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]Search the scriptures; for in them ye think ye have eternal life: and they are they which testify of me.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]And ye will not come to me, that ye might have life.
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]I receive not honour from men.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]But I know you, that ye have not the love of God in you.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]I am come in my Father's name, and ye receive me not: if another shall come in his own name, him ye will receive.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]How can ye believe, which receive honour one of another, and seek not the honour that cometh from God only?
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]Do not think that I will accuse you to the Father: there is one that accuseth you, even Moses, in whom ye trust.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]For had ye believed Moses, ye would have believed me; for he wrote of me.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]But if ye believe not his writings, how shall ye believe my words?
