\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And other sheep I have, which are not of this fold: them also I must bring, and they shall hear my voice; and there shall be one fold, and one shepherd.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Therefore doth my Father love me, because I lay down my life, that I might take it again.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]No man taketh it from me, but I lay it down of myself. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it again. This commandment have I received of my Father.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]There was a division therefore again among the Jews for these sayings.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And many of them said, He hath a devil, and is mad; why hear ye him?
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Others said, These are not the words of him that hath a devil. Can a devil open the eyes of the blind?
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And it was at Jerusalem the feast of the dedication, and it was winter.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And Jesus walked in the temple in Solomon's porch.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Then came the Jews round about him, and said unto him, How long dost thou make us to doubt? If thou be the Christ, tell us plainly.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Jesus answered them, I told you, and ye believed not: the works that I do in my Father's name, they bear witness of me.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]But ye believe not, because ye are not of my sheep, as I said unto you.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me:
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And I give unto them eternal life; and they shall never perish, neither shall any man pluck them out of my hand.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]My Father, which gave them me, is greater than all; and no man is able to pluck them out of my Father's hand.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]I and my Father are one.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Then the Jews took up stones again to stone him.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]Jesus answered them, Many good works have I shewed you from my Father; for which of those works do ye stone me?
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]The Jews answered him, saying, For a good work we stone thee not; but for blasphemy; and because that thou, being a man, makest thyself God.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Jesus answered them, Is it not written in your law, I said, Ye are gods?
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]If he called them gods, unto whom the word of God came, and the scripture cannot be broken;
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]Say ye of him, whom the Father hath sanctified, and sent into the world, Thou blasphemest; because I said, I am the Son of God?
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]If I do not the works of my Father, believe me not.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]But if I do, though ye believe not me, believe the works: that ye may know, and believe, that the Father is in me, and I in him.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]Therefore they sought again to take him: but he escaped out of their hand,
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]And went away again beyond Jordan into the place where John at first baptized; and there he abode.
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]And many resorted unto him, and said, John did no miracle: but all things that John spake of this man were true.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And many believed on him there.
