\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Now Jesus loved Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]When he had heard therefore that he was sick, he abode two days still in the same place where he was.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Then after that saith he to his disciples, Let us go into Judaea again.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]His disciples say unto him, Master, the Jews of late sought to stone thee; and goest thou thither again?
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Jesus answered, Are there not twelve hours in the day? If any man walk in the day, he stumbleth not, because he seeth the light of this world.
