\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Then said his disciples, Lord, if he sleep, he shall do well.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Howbeit Jesus spake of his death: but they thought that he had spoken of taking of rest in sleep.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Then said Jesus unto them plainly, Lazarus is dead.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And I am glad for your sakes that I was not there, to the intent ye may believe; nevertheless let us go unto him.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Then said Thomas, which is called Didymus, unto his fellowdisciples, Let us also go, that we may die with him.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Then when Jesus came, he found that he had lain in the grave four days already.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Now Bethany was nigh unto Jerusalem, about fifteen furlongs off:
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]And many of the Jews came to Martha and Mary, to comfort them concerning their brother.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Then Martha, as soon as she heard that Jesus was coming, went and met him: but Mary sat still in the house.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Then said Martha unto Jesus, Lord, if thou hadst been here, my brother had not died.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]But I know, that even now, whatsoever thou wilt ask of God, God will give it thee.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Jesus saith unto her, Thy brother shall rise again.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Martha saith unto him, I know that he shall rise again in the resurrection at the last day.
