\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]Jesus wept.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]Then said the Jews, Behold how he loved him!
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And some of them said, Could not this man, which opened the eyes of the blind, have caused that even this man should not have died?
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]Jesus therefore again groaning in himself cometh to the grave. It was a cave, and a stone lay upon it.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]Jesus said, Take ye away the stone. Martha, the sister of him that was dead, saith unto him, Lord, by this time he stinketh: for he hath been dead four days.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]Jesus saith unto her, Said I not unto thee, that, if thou wouldest believe, thou shouldest see the glory of God?
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]Then they took away the stone from the place where the dead was laid. And Jesus lifted up his eyes, and said, Father, I thank thee that thou hast heard me.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And I knew that thou hearest me always: but because of the people which stand by I said it, that they may believe that thou hast sent me.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]And when he thus had spoken, he cried with a loud voice, Lazarus, come forth.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]And he that was dead came forth, bound hand and foot with graveclothes: and his face was bound about with a napkin. Jesus saith unto them, Loose him, and let him go.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]Then many of the Jews which came to Mary, and had seen the things which Jesus did, believed on him.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]But some of them went their ways to the Pharisees, and told them what things Jesus had done.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]Then gathered the chief priests and the Pharisees a council, and said, What do we? for this man doeth many miracles.
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]If we let him thus alone, all men will believe on him: and the Romans shall come and take away both our place and nation.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]And one of them, named Caiaphas, being the high priest that same year, said unto them, Ye know nothing at all,
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]Nor consider that it is expedient for us, that one man should die for the people, and that the whole nation perish not.
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX]And this spake he not of himself: but being high priest that year, he prophesied that Jesus should die for that nation;
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]And not for that nation only, but that also he should gather together in one the children of God that were scattered abroad.
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]Then from that day forth they took counsel together for to put him to death.
