\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]And when the townclerk had appeased the people, he said, Ye men of Ephesus, what man is there that knoweth not how that the city of the Ephesians is a worshipper of the great goddess Diana, and of the image which fell down from Jupiter?
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]Seeing then that these things cannot be spoken against, ye ought to be quiet, and to do nothing rashly.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]For ye have brought hither these men, which are neither robbers of churches, nor yet blasphemers of your goddess.
