\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And how I kept back nothing that was profitable unto you, but have shewed you, and have taught you publicly, and from house to house,
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Testifying both to the Jews, and also to the Greeks, repentance toward God, and faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And now, behold, I go bound in the spirit unto Jerusalem, not knowing the things that shall befall me there:
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Save that the Holy Ghost witnesseth in every city, saying that bonds and afflictions abide me.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]But none of these things move me, neither count I my life dear unto myself, so that I might finish my course with joy, and the ministry, which I have received of the Lord Jesus, to testify the gospel of the grace of God.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And now, behold, I know that ye all, among whom I have gone preaching the kingdom of God, shall see my face no more.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Wherefore I take you to record this day, that I am pure from the blood of all men.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]For I have not shunned to declare unto you all the counsel of God.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Take heed therefore unto yourselves, and to all the flock, over the which the Holy Ghost hath made you overseers, to feed the church of God, which he hath purchased with his own blood.
