\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]For as many as have sinned without law shall also perish without law: and as many as have sinned in the law shall be judged by the law;
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX](For not the hearers of the law are just before God, but the doers of the law shall be justified.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]For when the Gentiles, which have not the law, do by nature the things contained in the law, these, having not the law, are a law unto themselves:
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Which shew the work of the law written in their hearts, their conscience also bearing witness, and their thoughts the mean while accusing or else excusing one another;)
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]In the day when God shall judge the secrets of men by Jesus Christ according to my gospel.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Behold, thou art called a Jew, and restest in the law, and makest thy boast of God,
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And knowest his will, and approvest the things that are more excellent, being instructed out of the law;
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]And art confident that thou thyself art a guide of the blind, a light of them which are in darkness,
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]An instructor of the foolish, a teacher of babes, which hast the form of knowledge and of the truth in the law.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Thou therefore which teachest another, teachest thou not thyself? thou that preachest a man should not steal, dost thou steal?
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Thou that sayest a man should not commit adultery, dost thou commit adultery? thou that abhorrest idols, dost thou commit sacrilege?
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Thou that makest thy boast of the law, through breaking the law dishonourest thou God?
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]For the name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles through you, as it is written.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]For circumcision verily profiteth, if thou keep the law: but if thou be a breaker of the law, thy circumcision is made uncircumcision.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Therefore if the uncircumcision keep the righteousness of the law, shall not his uncircumcision be counted for circumcision?
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And shall not uncircumcision which is by nature, if it fulfil the law, judge thee, who by the letter and circumcision dost transgress the law?
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]For he is not a Jew, which is one outwardly; neither is that circumcision, which is outward in the flesh:
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]But he is a Jew, which is one inwardly; and circumcision is that of the heart, in the spirit, and not in the letter; whose praise is not of men, but of God.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 3"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "W" 2 COND 90
hat advantage then hath the Jew? or what profit is there of circumcision?
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Much every way: chiefly, because that unto them were committed the oracles of God.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]For what if some did not believe? shall their unbelief make the faith of God without effect?
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]God forbid: yea, let God be true, but every man a liar; as it is written, That thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]But if our unrighteousness commend the righteousness of God, what shall we say? Is God unrighteous who taketh vengeance? (I speak as a man)
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]God forbid: for then how shall God judge the world?
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]For if the truth of God hath more abounded through my lie unto his glory; why yet am I also judged as a sinner?
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]And not rather, (as we be slanderously reported, and as some affirm that we say,) Let us do evil, that good may come? whose damnation is just.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]What then? are we better than they? No, in no wise: for we have before proved both Jews and Gentiles, that they are all under sin;
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]As it is written, There is none righteous, no, not one:
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]There is none that understandeth, there is none that seeketh after God.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]They are all gone out of the way, they are together become unprofitable; there is none that doeth good, no, not one.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Their throat is an open sepulchre; with their tongues they have used deceit; the poison of asps is under their lips:
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness:
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Their feet are swift to shed blood:
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Destruction and misery are in their ways:
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And the way of peace have they not known:
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]There is no fear of God before their eyes.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Now we know that what things soever the law saith, it saith to them who are under the law: that every mouth may be stopped, and all the world may become guilty before God.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Therefore by the deeds of the law there shall no flesh be justified in his sight: for by the law is the knowledge of sin.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]But now the righteousness of God without the law is manifested, being witnessed by the law and the prophets;
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Even the righteousness of God which is by faith of Jesus Christ unto all and upon all them that believe: for there is no difference:
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]For all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God;
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Being justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus:
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Whom God hath set forth to be a propitiation through faith in his blood, to declare his righteousness for the remission of sins that are past, through the forbearance of God;
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]To declare, I say, at this time his righteousness: that he might be just, and the justifier of him which believeth in Jesus.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]Where is boasting then? It is excluded. By what law? of works? Nay: but by the law of faith.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Therefore we conclude that a man is justified by faith without the deeds of the law.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Is he the God of the Jews only? is he not also of the Gentiles? Yes, of the Gentiles also:
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Seeing it is one God, which shall justify the circumcision by faith, and uncircumcision through faith.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Do we then make void the law through faith? God forbid: yea, we establish the law.
