now ye not, brethren, (for I speak to them that know the law,) how that the law hath dominion over a man as long as he liveth?
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]For the woman which hath an husband is bound by the law to her husband so long as he liveth; but if the husband be dead, she is loosed from the law of her husband.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]So then if, while her husband liveth, she be married to another man, she shall be called an adulteress: but if her husband be dead, she is free from that law; so that she is no adulteress, though she be married to another man.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]Wherefore, my brethren, ye also are become dead to the law by the body of Christ; that ye should be married to another, even to him who is raised from the dead, that we should bring forth fruit unto God.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]For when we were in the flesh, the motions of sins, which were by the law, did work in our members to bring forth fruit unto death.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]But now we are delivered from the law, that being dead wherein we were held; that we should serve in newness of spirit, and not in the oldness of the letter.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]What shall we say then? Is the law sin? God forbid. Nay, I had not known sin, but by the law: for I had not known lust, except the law had said, Thou shalt not covet.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]But sin, taking occasion by the commandment, wrought in me all manner of concupiscence. For without the law sin was dead.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]For I was alive without the law once: but when the commandment came, sin revived, and I died.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]And the commandment, which was ordained to life, I found to be unto death.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]For sin, taking occasion by the commandment, deceived me, and by it slew me.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Wherefore the law is holy, and the commandment holy, and just, and good.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Was then that which is good made death unto me? God forbid. But sin, that it might appear sin, working death in me by that which is good; that sin by the commandment might become exceeding sinful.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]For we know that the law is spiritual: but I am carnal, sold under sin.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]For that which I do I allow not: for what I would, that do I not; but what I hate, that do I.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]If then I do that which I would not, I consent unto the law that it is good.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Now then it is no more I that do it, but sin that dwelleth in me.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]For I know that in me (that is, in my flesh,) dwelleth no good thing: for to will is present with me; but how to perform that which is good I find not.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]For the good that I would I do not: but the evil which I would not, that I do.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Now if I do that I would not, it is no more I that do it, but sin that dwelleth in me.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]I find then a law, that, when I would do good, evil is present with me.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]For I delight in the law of God after the inward man:
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]But I see another law in my members, warring against the law of my mind, and bringing me into captivity to the law of sin which is in my members.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]O wretched man that I am! who shall deliver me from the body of this death?
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]I thank God through Jesus Christ our Lord. So then with the mind I myself serve the law of God; but with the flesh the law of sin.
