nd I, brethren, could not speak unto you as unto spiritual, but as unto carnal, even as unto babes in Christ.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]I have fed you with milk, and not with meat: for hitherto ye were not able to bear it, neither yet now are ye able.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]For ye are yet carnal: for whereas there is among you envying, and strife, and divisions, are ye not carnal, and walk as men?
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]For while one saith, I am of Paul; and another, I am of Apollos; are ye not carnal?
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Who then is Paul, and who is Apollos, but ministers by whom ye believed, even as the Lord gave to every man?
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]I have planted, Apollos watered; but God gave the increase.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]So then neither is he that planteth any thing, neither he that watereth; but God that giveth the increase.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Now he that planteth and he that watereth are one: and every man shall receive his own reward according to his own labour.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]For we are labourers together with God: ye are God's husbandry, ye are God's building.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]According to the grace of God which is given unto me, as a wise masterbuilder, I have laid the foundation, and another buildeth thereon. But let every man take heed how he buildeth thereupon.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]For other foundation can no man lay than that is laid, which is Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Now if any man build upon this foundation gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, stubble;
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Every man's work shall be made manifest: for the day shall declare it, because it shall be revealed by fire; and the fire shall try every man's work of what sort it is.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]If any man's work abide which he hath built thereupon, he shall receive a reward.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]If any man's work shall be burned, he shall suffer loss: but he himself shall be saved; yet so as by fire.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Know ye not that ye are the temple of God, and that the Spirit of God dwelleth in you?
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]If any man defile the temple of God, him shall God destroy; for the temple of God is holy, which temple ye are.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Let no man deceive himself. If any man among you seemeth to be wise in this world, let him become a fool, that he may be wise.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God. For it is written, He taketh the wise in their own craftiness.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And again, The Lord knoweth the thoughts of the wise, that they are vain.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Therefore let no man glory in men. For all things are your's;
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life, or death, or things present, or things to come; all are your's;
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And ye are Christ's; and Christ is God's.
