ut I determined this with myself, that I would not come again to you in heaviness.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]For if I make you sorry, who is he then that maketh me glad, but the same which is made sorry by me?
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And I wrote this same unto you, lest, when I came, I should have sorrow from them of whom I ought to rejoice; having confidence in you all, that my joy is the joy of you all.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]For out of much affliction and anguish of heart I wrote unto you with many tears; not that ye should be grieved, but that ye might know the love which I have more abundantly unto you.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]But if any have caused grief, he hath not grieved me, but in part: that I may not overcharge you all.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Sufficient to such a man is this punishment, which was inflicted of many.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]So that contrariwise ye ought rather to forgive him, and comfort him, lest perhaps such a one should be swallowed up with overmuch sorrow.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Wherefore I beseech you that ye would confirm your love toward him.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]For to this end also did I write, that I might know the proof of you, whether ye be obedient in all things.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]To whom ye forgive any thing, I forgive also: for if I forgave any thing, to whom I forgave it, for your sakes forgave I it in the person of Christ;
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Lest Satan should get an advantage of us: for we are not ignorant of his devices.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Furthermore, when I came to Troas to preach Christ's gospel, and a door was opened unto me of the Lord,
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]I had no rest in my spirit, because I found not Titus my brother: but taking my leave of them, I went from thence into Macedonia.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Now thanks be unto God, which always causeth us to triumph in Christ, and maketh manifest the savour of his knowledge by us in every place.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]For we are unto God a sweet savour of Christ, in them that are saved, and in them that perish:
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]To the one we are the savour of death unto death; and to the other the savour of life unto life. And who is sufficient for these things?
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]For we are not as many, which corrupt the word of God: but as of sincerity, but as of God, in the sight of God speak we in Christ.
