.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "B" 2 COND 90
e ye therefore followers of God, as dear children;
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And walk in love, as Christ also hath loved us, and hath given himself for us an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweetsmelling savour.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]But fornication, and all uncleanness, or covetousness, let it not be once named among you, as becometh saints;
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]Neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not convenient: but rather giving of thanks.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]For this ye know, that no whoremonger, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, hath any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Let no man deceive you with vain words: for because of these things cometh the wrath of God upon the children of disobedience.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Be not ye therefore partakers with them.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]For ye were sometimes darkness, but now are ye light in the Lord: walk as children of light:
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX](For the fruit of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth;)
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Proving what is acceptable unto the Lord.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]But all things that are reproved are made manifest by the light: for whatsoever doth make manifest is light.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Wherefore he saith, Awake thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead, and Christ shall give thee light.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools, but as wise,
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Redeeming the time, because the days are evil.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Wherefore be ye not unwise, but understanding what the will of the Lord is.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And be not drunk with wine, wherein is excess; but be filled with the Spirit;
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Giving thanks always for all things unto God and the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ;
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Submitting yourselves one to another in the fear of God.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as unto the Lord.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church: and he is the saviour of the body.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so let the wives be to their own husbands in every thing.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the church, and gave himself for it;
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]That he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word,
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]That he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot, or wrinkle, or any such thing; but that it should be holy and without blemish.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]So ought men to love their wives as their own bodies. He that loveth his wife loveth himself.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]For no man ever yet hated his own flesh; but nourisheth and cherisheth it, even as the Lord the church:
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]For we are members of his body, of his flesh, and of his bones.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and shall be joined unto his wife, and they two shall be one flesh.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]This is a great mystery: but I speak concerning Christ and the church.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Nevertheless let every one of you in particular so love his wife even as himself; and the wife see that she reverence her husband.
