ut of the times and the seasons, brethren, ye have no need that I write unto you.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]For yourselves know perfectly that the day of the Lord so cometh as a thief in the night.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]For when they shall say, Peace and safety; then sudden destruction cometh upon them, as travail upon a woman with child; and they shall not escape.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]But ye, brethren, are not in darkness, that that day should overtake you as a thief.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Ye are all the children of light, and the children of the day: we are not of the night, nor of darkness.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Therefore let us not sleep, as do others; but let us watch and be sober.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]For they that sleep sleep in the night; and they that be drunken are drunken in the night.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]But let us, who are of the day, be sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love; and for an helmet, the hope of salvation.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]For God hath not appointed us to wrath, but to obtain salvation by our Lord Jesus Christ,
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Who died for us, that, whether we wake or sleep, we should live together with him.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Wherefore comfort yourselves together, and edify one another, even as also ye do.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And we beseech you, brethren, to know them which labour among you, and are over you in the Lord, and admonish you;
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And to esteem them very highly in love for their work's sake. And be at peace among yourselves.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Now we exhort you, brethren, warn them that are unruly, comfort the feebleminded, support the weak, be patient toward all men.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]See that none render evil for evil unto any man; but ever follow that which is good, both among yourselves, and to all men.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Rejoice evermore.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Pray without ceasing.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]In every thing give thanks: for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus concerning you.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Quench not the Spirit.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Despise not prophesyings.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Prove all things; hold fast that which is good.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Abstain from all appearance of evil.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And the very God of peace sanctify you wholly; and I pray God your whole spirit and soul and body be preserved blameless unto the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Faithful is he that calleth you, who also will do it.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Brethren, pray for us.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Greet all the brethren with an holy kiss.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]I charge you by the Lord that this epistle be read unto all the holy brethren.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you. Amen.
