.\"
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 1"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "P" 2 COND 90
aul, a prisoner of Jesus Christ, and Timothy our brother, unto Philemon our dearly beloved, and fellowlabourer,
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And to our beloved Apphia, and Archippus our fellowsoldier, and to the church in thy house:
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]I thank my God, making mention of thee always in my prayers,
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Hearing of thy love and faith, which thou hast toward the Lord Jesus, and toward all saints;
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]That the communication of thy faith may become effectual by the acknowledging of every good thing which is in you in Christ Jesus.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]For we have great joy and consolation in thy love, because the bowels of the saints are refreshed by thee, brother.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Wherefore, though I might be much bold in Christ to enjoin thee that which is convenient,
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Yet for love's sake I rather beseech thee, being such an one as Paul the aged, and now also a prisoner of Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]I beseech thee for my son Onesimus, whom I have begotten in my bonds:
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Which in time past was to thee unprofitable, but now profitable to thee and to me:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Whom I have sent again: thou therefore receive him, that is, mine own bowels:
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Whom I would have retained with me, that in thy stead he might have ministered unto me in the bonds of the gospel:
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]But without thy mind would I do nothing; that thy benefit should not be as it were of necessity, but willingly.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]For perhaps he therefore departed for a season, that thou shouldest receive him for ever;
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Not now as a servant, but above a servant, a brother beloved, specially to me, but how much more unto thee, both in the flesh, and in the Lord?
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]If thou count me therefore a partner, receive him as myself.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]If he hath wronged thee, or oweth thee ought, put that on mine account;
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]I Paul have written it with mine own hand, I will repay it: albeit I do not say to thee how thou owest unto me even thine own self besides.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Yea, brother, let me have joy of thee in the Lord: refresh my bowels in the Lord.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Having confidence in thy obedience I wrote unto thee, knowing that thou wilt also do more than I say.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]But withal prepare me also a lodging: for I trust that through your prayers I shall be given unto you.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]There salute thee Epaphras, my fellowprisoner in Christ Jesus;
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Marcus, Aristarchus, Demas, Lucas, my fellowlabourers.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.
.\"
